      out.print(cdnurl);
      out.write("/intl/common/img/feature_Spreadsheet-Style-Builder.png\" alt=\"Social Collaboration Screenshot\"/>\r\n    <p style=\"width:290px;float:left;clear:left;\">We want to make building DB applications as easy as using spreadsheets. Simply type the field names that you would like to create as in spreadsheet, and the fields are created. It can't get simpler than this.</p>\r\n    <p style=\"width:290px;float:left;clear:left;\">Creating complex forms with multiple details is incredibly simple with Ragic. Just put field headers horizontally next to each other, and a detail table is created with these fields.</p>\r\n    <p style=\"width:290px;float:left;clear:left;\">Notice there's no need to create tables or objects or any database trouble. Why? We'll let you in on a secret, Ragic Builder is not based on database tables, that's why we have all this amazing flexibility.</p>\r\n    <p style=\"width:290px;float:left;clear:left;\">Like spreadsheets, tons of settings can be configured on each fields and forms to make sure the app works the way you want it to.</p>\r\n");
